  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      With early screening and appropriate iron supplementation, iron deficiency in the first year
      of life can be prevented in breastfed infants.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Infants with low ferritin at 1 month are at high risk of iron deficiency. They will receive
      iron drops starting at 2 months. All other infants are at low risk of iron deficiency. All
      infants will receive iron-fortified cereal starting at 4 months of age.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
